學習規範 Course Policy
	    1. You are expected to attend every class. If, due to illness, accident, or family crisis, you must miss a class, please notify the Professors before class via e-mail, voice mail.  If a class is missed, it is assumed that the student will contact a classmate for notes and announcements.  Please do not ask the course instructor for missed notes.
2. It is expected that each student will check Moodle once within 24 hours before each lecture and lab for any new handouts and/or notices.
3. All written assignments must be TYPED, double-spaced and use APA format for citations and references. Points will be deducted for poor grammar and spelling. Although rewrites are not usual, in certain circumstances, you may be asked to do one. In this case, the maximum grade on a rewrite will be 80. Grading of written assignments will reflect timeliness, completeness, quality of the information and clarity and depth of reasoning, and professional writing.
4. Activity Analysis Reports are to be turned in by April 11th, May 16th, and June 13th.  Five points will be deducted for each day an assignment is late, unless an extension has been provided.  It is assumed that the student will keep copies of all written assignments that are handed in.      

