課程概述 Course Description
       This course contains 1 lecturer and 1 practice credits. Practice is emphasized to facilitate experiential learning about professional issues. It reviews some professional basics and introduces some advanced practice guidelines to prepare the occupational therapy students for fieldwork practice. Through the semester, the crafts, modalities, and techniques are introduced with practice experience. The issues of therapeutic relationship, clinical reasoning, activity analysis and application are addressed to build up the professional identity. Students will learn general skills of activity analysis, adaptation, and application of occupation. The application sessions of this course are designed to introduce the student to various aspects of occupation as they relate to the generic practice of occupational therapy, e.g. activity analysis, application, and adaptation. Acquisition of skills in performing and analyzing activities will be stressed. Activities include needlework, crafts, culinary, carpentry, and occupational functioning.This course contains 1 lecturer and 1 practice credits. Practice is emphasized to facilitate experiential learning about professional issues. It reviews some professional basics and introduces some advanced practice guidelines to prepare the occupational therapy students for fieldwork practice. Through the semester, the crafts, modalities, and techniques are introduced with practice experience. The issues of therapeutic relationship, clinical reasoning, activity analysis and application are addressed to build up the professional identity. Students will learn general skills of activity analysis, adaptation, and application of occupation. The application sessions of this course are designed to introduce the student to various aspects of occupation as they relate to the generic practice of occupational therapy, e.g. activity analysis, application, and adaptation. Acquisition of skills in performing and analyzing activities will be stressed. Activities include needlework, crafts, culinary, carpentry, and occupational functioning.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    Upon completion of this course the students should be able to:
1. identify and describe the terms and concepts introduced in this course.
2. describe the experience and know-how of the therapeutic modalities which are introduced for potential use for OT practice.
3. develop professional attitude and skills to apply appropriate guidelines with regard to the core concept of "occupation".    

